        {
            "title": "聯儲會的庫克稱自己縱使只是暫時離任 或將造成金融市場混亂和破壞",
            "description": "<div class=\"atoms\"><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">【彭博】— 聯儲會理事麗莎·庫克的律師敦促美國最高法院，在美國總統<a class=\"link\" data-i13n=\"sec:content-canvas;subsec:anchor_text;elm:context_link\" data-ylk=\"slk:特朗普;sec:content-canvas;subsec:anchor_text;elm:context_link;itc:0\" href=\"https://hk.finance.yahoo.com/tag/特朗普\">特朗普</a>試圖解僱她的期間，讓她繼續任職；並警告說，即使她只是暫時離任，也可能為金融市場帶來「混亂和破壞」。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">她的律師周四在提交的陳述中寫道，批准司法部允許特朗普立即解僱她的請求「將敲響央行獨立性的喪鐘，而這種獨立性曾幫助美國經濟成為全球最強大的國家」。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">司法部曾經請求最高法院允許特朗普解僱庫克，同時正在對抗下級法院的一項裁決。庫克是由前總統喬·拜登任命，特朗普8月底宣布將因抵押貸款詐欺指控而解僱她，她斷然否認該指控並持續擔任該職。</p><div class=\"bg-card-bg-1 -mx-5 -mt-2 mb-3 pb-3 md:-mx-0\"><div class=\"text-px14 text-gandalf py-1 text-center leading-5\">廣告</div><div class=\"mx-auto text-center min-w-[300px] min-h-[250px]\" id=\"sda-inbody-75ad0d99-41fb-369e-a275-f708de10b4a2-1-iframe\"><div class=\"bg-dirty-seagull text-px12 text-dolphin mx-auto hidden items-center justify-center only:flex w-[300px] h-[250px]\">廣告</div></div></div><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit\"><img alt=\"聯儲會理事麗莎·庫克資料來源：彭博社\" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"534\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/O9zB06bzZNBhEbn1t5MfOA--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTU0MDtjZj13ZWJw/https://media.zenfs.com/en/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/da1a284e91786d84f7f84615cca157b5\" width=\"950\"/><figcaption class=\"text-px14 text-dolphin mt-2 wrap-anywhere\" style=\"max-width:950px\">聯儲會理事麗莎·庫克資料來源：彭博社</figcaption></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">最高法院為該案的書面陳述設定了一個快速時間表，但尚未明確透露何時將作出裁決。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">原文標題Fed’s Cook Warns Supreme Court of Market ‘Chaos’ If She’s Fired</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">—聯合報導 Greg Stohr.</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">More stories like this are available on <a class=\"link\" data-i13n=\"cpos:1;pos:1\" data-ylk=\"slk:bloomberg.com;cpos:1;pos:1;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">bloomberg.com</a></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">©2025 Bloomberg L.P.</p></div>",
